  "title": "LifetimeFunction",
  "description": "Lifetime-parameterised function that produces a deterministic `T` for a given lifetime ratio `t` in `[0, 1]`. Used by per-frame update modules that interpolate over particle lifetime — `ColorOverLifetime` (ColorGradient), `ScaleOverLifetime` (Curve), etc. Mutable-target rule: same as Distribution — pass your own scratch via `out` for hot loops, omit for one-off calls.",
